Wash and dry produce. Quarter @lemon{1}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb} (all for 4 servings). Thinly slice @chili pepper{1}.

In a small #pot, combine @basmati rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, in a medium microwave-safe #bowl, combine @sugar{3/4%tsp} (1 1/2 tsp for 4 servings) and juice from two lemon wedges (four wedges for 4); stir to dissolve. Add @shredded red cabbage{4%oz} and 2 TBSP water (4 TBSP for 4); season with 1/4 tsp salt (1/2 tsp for 4) and @pepper{}. Microwave for ~{1%minute}. Taste and season with salt if needed. Set aside to pickle, stirring occasionally, until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a large #pan over medium-high heat. Add @curry powder{1%tbsp} and cook, stirring constantly, until fragrant, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Add @ground turkey{10%oz} and @garlic powder{1%tsp}; season with salt (we used 3/4 tsp; 1 1/2 tsp salt for 4 servings) and pepper. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until lightly browned, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add scallion whites, @ginger{1/2%tbsp}(minced) (1 TBSP for 4), and half the chili. (Use all the chili if you like spicy food, or leave it out if you're not a fan of heat!) Cook until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in @apricot jam{1}, @sour cream{2%tbsp}, @dried apricots{1%oz}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, 1/2 cup water (3/4 cup for 4 servings), and a squeeze of lemon juice to pan with turkey. Cook until liquid has slightly reduced and turkey is cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Fluff rice with a #fork; taste and season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice and turkey mixture between #bowls{}. Top with cabbage and garnish with scallion greens. Serve.